p: In the District Court Judicial District of W.T.
W. H. Barret and Isabella Barret

Wherein an application has been made by Charles Gahres and Martha Gahres Guardians of Ella Dora Cravens a minor persuaded statute to the Hon. Joseph M. Lewis Judge of the W T District Courst, First Judicial District of Washington Teritory and on order granted for a Writ of Habeas Corpus commanding that W.H. Barret and Isabella Barret to appear and produce the body of Ella Dora Cravens and show cause the Ella Dora Cravens should be returned to guardian Charles Gahres and Martha J. Gahres

Therfore in the name of the United States You are commanded to appear before the Hon Joseph R. Lewis Judge at a Court to be held of Chambers in the Court House in the city of Walla Walla County of Walla Walla and Teritory of Washington on Monday September 12th 1873 at 10 oclock AM then and then of produce the body of the said Ella Dora Cravens and show cursory who the said minor child is withheld from the care and custody of affilants and for care said in this preceedings and would further under of the on be in .
Witness the Hon Joseph R Lewis Judge and the lead of Disct Court the 29th day of August A.D. 1873
